A RECORDING, allegedly of Mpumalanga’s MEC for Sports and RecreationLindiwe Ntshalintshalidiscussing government deals, is an attempt to discredit her ahead of the ANC’s elective conference in the province, she told the SABC. The recording was aired by the SABC yesterday morning and details alleged kickbacks with an unidentified man. The recording alsoallegedly containsNtshalintshali’s plan to fire key staff members. Responding to theallegations, Ntshalintshali told the public broadcaster it formed part of a plan todiscredit her ahead of the party’s conference. She said the authenticity of the recording would need to be verified and that her right to privacy may have beeninfringed upon. ANC spokesperson Dakota Legoete said the recording and its authenticity would be investigated by the governing party. Said Dakota: “Upon us making an internal investigation, [we will] bring the comrade in question before theleadership of the ANC, the Top Six. “We’ll decide on what course of action to takethereafter, in line with the provisions of the ANC’sconstitution.”              – News24